src/lib/components/DashPlayer.react.js.description:
A Dash component for playing a variety of URLs, including file paths,
YouTube, Facebook, Twitch, SoundCloud, Streamable, Vimeo, Wistia, Mixcloud,
and DailyMotion.

methods.name: updateIntervals
methods.docblock:
When one of the interval props are changed, this clears the currently
assigned handle and set it to the new interval value. It works for
currentTime, duration and secondsLoaded.
methods.description:
When one of the interval props are changed, this clears the currently
assigned handle and set it to the new interval value. It works for
currentTime, duration and secondsLoaded.

methods.name: setSeekTo
methods.docblock:
Applies the seekTo() method to the player if the seekTo prop
contains any value, then set seekTo to null. If seekTo was already
null, it doesn't do anything.
methods.description:

contains any value, then set seekTo to null. If seekTo was already

id.description: The ID used to identify this compnent in Dash callbacks

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called whenever any of the
properties change

url.description:
The url of a video or song to play
◦  Can be an array or MediaStream object

playing.description: Set to true or false to pause or play the media

loop.description: Set to true or false to loop the media

controls.description:
Set to true or false to display native player controls
Vimeo, Twitch and Wistia player will always display controls

volume.description:
Set the volume of the player, between 0 and 1
null uses default volume on all players

muted.description:
Mutes the player
Only works if volume is set

playbackRate.description:
Set the playback rate of the player
Only supported by YouTube, Wistia, and file paths

width.description: Set the width of the player

height.description: Set the height of the player

style.description: Add inline styles to the root element

playsinline.description:
Applies the html5 playsinline attribute where supported, which allows
videos to be played inline and will not automatically enter fullscreen
mode when playback begins (for iOS).

currentTime.description: Returns the number of seconds that have been played

secondsLoaded.description: Returns the number of seconds that have been loaded

duration.description: Returns the duration (in seconds) of the currently playing media

intervalCurrentTime.description: Interval in milliseconds at which currenTtime prop is updated.

intervalSecondsLoaded.description: Interval in milliseconds at which secondsLoaded prop is updated.

intervalDuration.description: Interval in milliseconds at which duration prop is updated.

seekTo.description: Seek to the given number of seconds, or fraction if amount is between 0 and 1
